TITLE: Wildfires Rage Through Greece As Thousands Are Evacuated
SUMMARY: Three large fires and dozens of smaller ones are burning throughout the country. People continue to wait in lines to board rescue ferries evacuating people from the island of Evia.

TITLE: Heavy Rains Lead To Flash Flooding In Eastern Nebraska
SUMMARY: Water flooded downtown streets and some 18,000 residents experienced power outages as heavy rains, high winds and hail battered Omaha, Neb.

TITLE: Health Experts Fear A Spread Of COVID As Motorcyclists Gather In South Dakota
SUMMARY: Hundreds of thousands of bikers are traveling to the Sturgis Motorcycle Rally in South Dakota again this year. Last year's rally was linked to several hundred cases.

TITLE: California's Dixie Fire Is Now The 2nd Largest In State History
SUMMARY: Northern California's Dixie Fire, which has destroyed hundreds of buildings and entire communities, is now considered the second largest in state history.

TITLE: Paris Has Taken The Torch From Tokyo For The 2024 Summer Olympic Games
SUMMARY: A celebration in Paris debuted the Olympic flag flying from the Eiffel Tower as the French city prepares to host the 2024 summer Olympic games.

TITLE: The Taliban Has Seized 2 More Provincial Capitals In Afghanistan As U.S. Exit Nears
SUMMARY: Taliban gains in two key cities on Sunday are the latest locations to be overtaken by the group since it began a sweeping military offensive in May.

TITLE: United States Barely Edges Out China For Most Gold Medals At Tokyo Olympics
SUMMARY: For the seventh Olympic games in a row, the United States took home more medals than any country. But in the gold-medal race, they just barely edged China.

TITLE: The Best Photos From The Closing Ceremony Of The Tokyo Olympics
SUMMARY: After 17 days of Olympic competition that was far different than usual due to COVID-19 restrictions, Tokyo celebrated its closing ceremony Sunday with artistic performances and a light show.

TITLE: Bobby Bowden, One Of College Football's Winningest Coaches Ever, Dies
SUMMARY: Bobby Bowden won 377 games in his career, including two national titles, and took the Florida State University Seminoles to post-season bowl games in 27 consecutive years.

TITLE: You're Going To Hear A Lot About The 'Byrd Rule' Soon â€” Who Is This Byrd Man?
SUMMARY: As Democrats try to pass their massive multi-trillion-dollar spending bill with a simple majority vote, lots of things might be included but other things might not. And it all goes back to one man.

TITLE: Closing Ceremony Caps Off A Dramatic, Bittersweet And Ultimately Uplifting Olympics
SUMMARY: The ceremony organizers used artistic elements to show the athletes a taste of ordinary life in Japan, something they haven't been exposed to due to pandemic restrictions.

TITLE: The 14 Moments That Swept Us Away At The Tokyo Olympics
SUMMARY: NPR's team in Tokyo put together our favorite moments of the Games, where participants showed their athleticism, sportsmanship, and what motivated them to compete.

TITLE: U.S. Women's Volleyball Team Wins First Ever Olympic Gold Medal
SUMMARY: The U.S. defeated Brazil in straight sets to win its first Olympic gold medal. It was the U.S.'s sixth volleyball medal overall and the fourth Olympics in a row the U.S. medaled.

TITLE: U.S. Women's Basketball Wins Olympic Gold For The 7th Straight Time
SUMMARY: The U.S. women have not lost a game at the Olympics since the 1992 Games in Barcelona, a remarkable stretch of 55 straight victories and seven gold medals.

TITLE: German Modern Pentathlon Coach Disqualified For Punching A Horse
SUMMARY: Kim Raisner violated the rules at the Olympic Games when she lightly punched a reluctant horse that was refusing to ride.
